com.github.btrekkie.graph.dual

Class DualGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.btrekkie.graph.dual.DualGraph

  • public class DualGraph
extends java.lang.Object
    The dual of a certain planar Graph (the "primal graph"), with self loops removed, relative to a certain planar embedding. The dual H of a graph G is a graph with one vertex for each face in G, including the external face, and an edge between each pair of vertices corresponding to two faces in G separated by an edge. The dual is a MultiGraph.

      • graph

        public final MultiGraph graph
        The dual graph.

      • edgeToDualEdge

        public java.util.Map<UnorderedPair<Vertex>,UnorderedPair<MultiVertex>> edgeToDualEdge
        A map from each edge in the primal graph to the corresponding edge in "graph". Each edge is represented as a pair of its endpoints. It includes self-loop edges in the dual, represented as UnorderedPairs with the same value twice.

      • dualEdgeToEdges

        public java.util.Map<UnorderedPair<MultiVertex>,java.util.Collection<UnorderedPair<Vertex>>> dualEdgeToEdges
        A map from each edge in "graph" to a collection of the corresponding edges in the primal graph. Each edge is represented as a pair of its endpoints. It includes self-loop edges in the dual, represented as UnorderedPairs with the same value twice.
